item.title: Need help with a 562 client / khanz 562 ip changer
item.dc:creator: @abcpker711 abcpker711
item.description:
@abcpker711 wrote:

See, I’ve tried to explain this to many people on MoparScape, and RuneLocus… the thing is that the Kahnz IP-Changer Client is a 562 Client. Obviously the source you have is 569. If you go to upload a server, you’ll see “508, 562, and 569+” If your going to download a 569 source, then your going to want to download a 569 Client, and just go into the SRC file, search for “Client.java” and open it. Then what your going to want to do is search “ip:” then you will see “TestScape.no-ip.biz” and you change it to YOUR or the server your trying to login to’s IP-Address… then save it obviously. Then go all the way back to “Build” and and click it. Now this is even more complex then the step you have pulled before, if your “Build.cmd/exe” file says that it cannot detect a certain blah blah blah, then you need to right click it, click “Edit” then it will show you a notepad type deal, and you edit the java version to your java version…

Example: Jdk_0.6_1.2.3…
If yours is Jdk_0.6.1.3.3… then change it to that.

NOTE: Those are not actual JDK types, so please do not comment talking trash upon this post.

Thank-you. Hope I was of service.
